<br>
Tip #1:<br>
<br>
Master trade skills.  Not necessarily YOUR tradeskills, mind you, but others.  Find out who need what components for what, and how much they sell for in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Bazaar</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Collect them in your travels, mine NPC merchants for them, and maybe even scooping up very underpriced components and resell them at below average prices.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.EQTraders.com">EQTrader's Corner</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> is a treasure trove of information.<br>
<br>
Tip #2:<br>
<br>
Learn the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Bazaar</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Watch the prices, see what sells, what is undersupplied, what is oversupplied.  Get yourself a nest egg, and invest it.  Buy low, and sell below average.  Since there are so many items, I find it best to specialize in a particular class's gears, or a small number of classes' gear.  Read the forums and keep up on what gear is hot and what is not.  Find undervalued items, that is items with decent stats that sell for way under what other items with similar stats.<br>
<br>
Tip #3:<br>
<br>
Learn the loot tables.  Find what drops stuff in the 3-5 plat range, like fine steel.  Giants are usually good eating.  Although magic items are generally underpriced, you might try to farm specific items.  To learn what items drop where, try:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqmaps.com">EQMaps</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br>
<br>
And everyone is welcome to post and ask questions, regardless of level.  The only thing I ask is that you take advantage of the topic specific forums, and see if the answers you seek are already there.  Try to keep GENERAL from drowning in posts that belong in other forums, and maybe post there first.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Razamatazz Pizzazz</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
